name: nixtla
description: TimeGPT-1: production ready pre-trained Time Series Foundation Model  for forecasting and anomaly detection. Generative pretrained transformer for time series trained on over 100B data points. It's capable of accurately predicting various domains such as retail, electricity, finance, and IoT with just a few lines of code ðŸš€.
readme_summary: TimeGPT-1 is a production-ready, pre-trained transformer model for time series analysis. It excels at forecasting and anomaly detection across diverse domains like retail, electricity, and finance, requiring minimal code for accurate predictions.
key_features: Production-ready generative pretrained transformer for time series
Support for multiple programming languages via API
primary_use_case: Time series forecasting and anomaly detection
cover_image_prompt: A wise, ancient clockmaker meticulously assembling intricate gears and springs, representing historical time series data. As the clockwork mechanism comes to life, it projects a clear, glowing arrow pointing into the future, symbolizing accurate forecasting. Around the workshop, subtle digital interfaces display fluctuating graphs and anomaly alerts, hinting at the underlying AI. The clockmaker's tools are sleek and modern, blending traditional craftsmanship with advanced technology. The scene is bathed in warm, focused light, emphasizing precision and insight. The overall style is a detailed 3D isometric illustration, with a color palette of deep blues, warm brass, and glowing white accents, conveying both reliability and innovation.

name: freecut
description: FreeCut is a professional-grade video editor that runs entirely in your browser. Professional video editing, zero installation. Create stunning videos with multi-track editing, keyframe animations, real-time preview, and high-quality exports.
readme_summary: FreeCut is a powerful, open-source video editor that runs entirely within your web browser. It offers professional-grade features like multi-track editing, keyframe animation, and real-time preview, all without requiring any installation or server-side processing, leveraging modern web APIs for local editing.
key_features: Local editing using WebCodecs, OPFS, File System Access API
Multi-track timeline (video, audio, text, image, shape)
Keyframe animation with Bezier curve editor
CSS and Canvas effects, Glitch effects, Overlays, Presets
Real-time canvas preview with transform gizmo
In-browser rendering and export (MP4, MOV, WebM, MKV, MP3, AAC, WAV)
Import media via File System Access API (up to 5 GB)
primary_use_case: To provide a professional, feature-rich video editing experience directly in the web browser, accessible to anyone without installation or complex setup.
cover_image_prompt: A digital artist sitting at a sleek, minimalist desk, with a glowing, ethereal browser window open before them. Inside the browser window, a complex video editing timeline is visualized as a flowing river of light, with different colored streams representing video, audio, and text tracks. The artist is using a stylus to sculpt and arrange these streams, transforming raw footage (represented by shimmering digital particles flowing from the left) into a polished, cinematic scene (emanating as a radiant light from the right). Subtle UI elements of FreeCut are visible on a secondary screen, and the overall mood is one of creative flow and effortless digital creation. The style is a 3D isometric illustration with a clean, modern aesthetic and vibrant, contrasting colors.

name: bg-remove
description: Free image background removal - private, client-side and powered by Transformers.js
readme_summary: This repository provides a client-side, privacy-focused web application for removing backgrounds from images using machine learning models powered by Transformers.js. It offers one-click removal, custom background options, and local processing without server uploads, with optional WebGPU acceleration for enhanced performance.
key_features: Custom background color and image selection
Download options for transparent and colored backgrounds
primary_use_case: Removing image backgrounds directly in the user's browser for privacy and speed.
cover_image_prompt: A magical digital artist's easel in a clean, modern studio. On the easel, a plain photograph of a person is being transformed: the background is dissolving into shimmering digital particles, revealing a vibrant, custom-designed landscape behind the person. The artist, represented by a stylized cursor or a glowing brush, is effortlessly guiding this transformation. Small, subtle UI elements like a color palette and a download icon float near the easel. The overall mood is one of effortless creation and digital magic, emphasizing the 'bg-remove' name subtly etched on the easel. 3D isometric illustration style, bright and clean lighting, focus on the transformation process.

name: ArrowDL
description: ArrowDL (Arrow Downloader) is a download manager for Windows, MacOS and Linux
readme_summary: ArrowDL is a cross-platform download manager for Windows, macOS, and Linux, designed to efficiently download various types of content from the web. It integrates with web browsers via extensions and features an embedded web engine for independent operation.
key_features: Standalone download manager for Windows, MacOS, and Linux
WebExtensions support for Mozilla Firefox and other browsers
Embedded web engine (Google Gumbo Parser or Chromium)
Supports torrents, YouTube, and batch downloads
primary_use_case: Downloading various types of web content, including videos, torrents, and batch files, through a dedicated download manager application with browser integration.
cover_image_prompt: A stylized, friendly robot with multiple arms, each holding a different type of digital content (a video play button, a torrent file icon, a stack of documents). The robot is efficiently sorting and directing these items into a large, organized digital vault labeled 'ArrowDL'. Streams of data flow from various browser windows and web pages towards the robot. The background is a clean, modern interface with subtle code elements and progress bars. The overall mood is efficient and helpful. 3D isometric illustration style with bright, clean colors and clear iconography.

name: daktilo
description: Turn your keyboard into a typewriter! ðŸ“‡
readme_summary: Daktilo is a Rust-based command-line tool that emulates the sound of a typewriter with every keystroke. It offers various sound presets and allows for custom sound configurations to enhance the typing experience.
key_features: Built-in sound presets (default, basic, musicbox, ducktilo, drumkit, spark)
primary_use_case: To provide a nostalgic and engaging typing experience by simulating typewriter sounds through a command-line interface.
cover_image_prompt: A vintage, ornate typewriter sits on a wooden desk. Instead of ink, streams of colorful, glowing digital particles flow from the typewriter's keys as they are struck. Each particle represents a sound wave, with some particles forming subtle musical notes and others resembling a duck's quack or a drumbeat. In the background, a modern computer screen displays abstract sound visualizations, hinting at the software controlling the effect. The overall mood is whimsical and nostalgic, blending old-world charm with modern digital flair. The style should be a 3D isometric illustration with a warm, inviting color palette.
